title: Milwaukee
summary: Milwaukee (/mɪlˈwɔːki/ mil-WAW-kee)[13] is the largest city in the U.S. state of Wisconsin, and the fifth-largest city in the Midwestern United States.[14] The seat of Milwaukee County, the city is located on Lake Michigan's southwestern shore, and was incorporated in 1846. As of the 2020 census, Milwaukee had a population of 577,222, a decrease from 594,833 in 2010.[15] It is the 31st largest city in the United States[16][17] and the fourth-largest city situated along one of the Great Lakes.
